ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.96                 Enzyme
NAME        avermitilol synthase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     avermitilol hydrolase (cyclizing, avermitilol-forming)
REACTION    (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate + H2O = avermitilol + diphosphate [RN:R09896]
ALL_REAC    R09896
SUBSTRATE   (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C00448];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     avermitilol [CPD:C20181];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     Requires Mg2+. The recombinent enzyme gives avermitilol (85%) plus traces of germacrene A, germacrene B and viridiflorol. The (1S)-hydrogen of farnesyl diphosphate is retained.
